title: S.J. football: Haddonfield's DeLano wins 100th game
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports NONLEAGUE
Collingswood 25, Gateway 0: Dashon Burdett rushed for 196 yards and two touchdowns to lead the home team. Jahmir King added 101 yards and a TD on 10 carries. 
WEST JERSEY ROYAL 
Bishop Eustace 21, Cumberland 0: Kevin Lammers finished with 86 rushing yards, two interceptions, and a 53-yard punt return to spark the hosts. Wesley Payne ran for 50 yards rushing and made 11 tackles. Rob Dunn had nine tackles Jack Smith made six. 
WEST JERSEY COLONIAL 
Lenape 41, Allentown 7: Joseph Kellum ran in two early touchdowns and the eighth-ranked Indians rolled at home. Bryce Long threw two touchdowns and ran in another. Lenape has allowed just 21 points this season. 
WEST JERSEY CONSTITUTION 
Moorestown 35, Triton 6: Tom Bolte caught two touchdown passes to lead the visitors. 
Paul VI 29, Winslow Township 6: Donnelly Shuler returned an interception 60 yards in the first quarter to put the visiting No. 10 Eagles ahead by 10-0. Matt Vitale threw two touchdowns and also ran one in. 
WEST JERSEY NATIONAL 
Hammonton 41, Clearview 21: Mitchell Vitali rushed 16 times for 104 yards and a touchdown to lead the visiting No. 5 Blue Devils. Izick Flores added 96 yards on the ground. Clearview's Issac Murphy rushed for 102 yards. 
WEST JERSEY FREEDOM 
Palmyra 17, Florence 7: Joey Foga ran in an 80-yard touchdown in the first quarter to put the visitors ahead by 10-0. 
CAPE-ATLANTIC AMERICAN 
St. Augustine 27, Mainland 3: Kyle Dobbins piled up 206 yards on 22 carries to lead the No. 2 Hermits at home. Jose Tabora rushed for 40 yards and threw for 58.
